12:06.375 --> 12:08.333
MM.

12:08.333 --> 12:09.708
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

12:09.708 --> 12:10.542
ALL RIGHT.

12:10.542 --> 12:13.375
♪ DID I DO RIGHT? ♪

12:13.375 --> 12:16.708
♪ DID I DO WHAT I HAD TO? ♪

12:16.708 --> 12:22.708
♪ I'VE LIVED A LIFE ♪

12:22.708 --> 12:28.333
♪ OF GOOD INTENTIONS ♪

12:28.333 --> 12:33.750
♪ I MEANT TO DO RIGHT ♪

12:33.750 --> 12:42.583
♪ BUT I LIVED A LIFE ♪

12:42.583 --> 12:46.750
♪ I LIVED A LIFE
OF GOOD INTENTIONS ♪

12:46.750 --> 12:50.000
♪ OF GOOD INTENTIONS ♪♪

13:07.708 --> 13:10.083
I THOUGHT ALEX
WAS SMILING,

13:10.083 --> 13:10.959
BUT IT TURNS OUT
HE JUST HAD GAS.

13:10.959 --> 13:13.375
I'M GOING
TO GET GOING.

13:13.375 --> 13:14.625
WHAT'S WRONG?

13:14.625 --> 13:15.834
NOTHING.

13:15.834 --> 13:16.959
I THOUGHT YOU HAD

13:16.959 --> 13:18.458
A LOT OF READING
TO DO, DAWSON.

13:18.458 --> 13:21.041
UM, I'VE DONE ENOUGH
READING FOR TODAY.

13:42.291 --> 13:45.166
HEY, MAN, DOCK PARTY,
TONIGHT, 8:00, BAILEY'S WHARF.

13:45.166 --> 13:48.208
BE THERE!

13:48.208 --> 13:49.750
WHAT'S GOING ON?

13:49.750 --> 13:51.125
I'M THROWING A PARTY.

13:51.125 --> 13:52.125
WHY?

13:52.125 --> 13:53.125
OH, YOU KNOW,

13:53.125 --> 13:54.458
I'M EXPANDING
MY HORIZONS.

13:54.458 --> 13:55.834
I'M GETTING OLDER.
THOUGHT I'D BRANCH OUT.

13:55.834 --> 13:57.083
TAKE SOME NEW CHANCES.

13:57.083 --> 14:00.083
I ACCIDENTALLY READ
SOMETHING LAST NIGHT

14:00.083 --> 14:01.041
IN JOEY'S JOURNAL.

14:01.041 --> 14:01.875
HEY, WANT ONE OF THESE?

14:01.875 --> 14:03.834
QUOTE, "I'M
SO SICK OF DAWSON

14:03.834 --> 14:05.250
"AND HIS STUPID
HORROR MOVIE.

14:05.250 --> 14:07.250
"I WISH I COULD TELL HIM
HOW TERRIBLE IT IS.

14:07.250 --> 14:09.542
HOW STUPID AND PUTRID
AND RANCID AND..."

14:09.542 --> 14:11.583
IT'S AWFUL.

14:11.583 --> 14:13.083
SO WHAT?

14:13.083 --> 14:14.875
I MEAN, AT LEAST
SHE DIDN'T TELL YOU

14:14.875 --> 14:15.708
THAT THE SIGHT OF YOU
GIVES HER DRY HEAVES,

14:15.708 --> 14:19.417
OR THAT YOU'RE
A SELF-CENTERED,

14:19.417 --> 14:20.625
SELF-ABSORBED, SELFISH--

14:20.625 --> 14:22.375
YEAH,

14:22.375 --> 14:23.291
BUT SHE OBVIOUSLY
HAS OPINIONS ABOUT ME

14:23.291 --> 14:25.625
THAT SHE HASN'T
BEEN HONEST ABOUT.

14:25.625 --> 14:27.125
SHE SAID I WAS

14:27.125 --> 14:29.500
"A TALENTLESS DREAMER
WITH NO CINEMATIC FUTURE."

14:29.500 --> 14:30.834
OKAY, NO OFFENSE,
DAWSON,

14:30.834 --> 14:32.792
BUT I DON'T THINK ANYBODY CARES.

14:32.792 --> 14:34.500
I CARE, PACEY,

14:34.500 --> 14:36.708
AND I COULD HONESTLY
USE SOME ADVICE HERE.

14:36.708 --> 14:38.750
OH, YOU WANT SOME ADVICE?

14:38.750 --> 14:40.250
HOW ABOUT THIS?

14:40.250 --> 14:42.041
YOUR LIFE
IS NOT THAT INTERESTING.

14:42.041 --> 14:43.166
WHAT?

14:43.166 --> 14:46.041
YOU KNOW, I AM SO SICK AND TIRED
OF HEARING

14:46.041 --> 14:48.041
ABOUT YOU AND JOEY'S
BORING LITTLE MINI-DRAMAS,

14:48.041 --> 14:49.583
I'M GOING TO START
TEARING OUT MY FINGERNAILS

14:49.583 --> 14:50.375
FOR RELIEF.

14:50.375 --> 14:53.125
GET OVER YOURSELF,
DAWSON!

14:53.125 --> 14:54.000
DEAL.

14:59.208 --> 14:59.708
YOU WORK AT
THE ICE HOUSE,

14:59.708 --> 15:01.542
DON'T YOU?

15:01.542 --> 15:02.708
I SAW YOU THERE
TWO NIGHTS AGO.

15:02.708 --> 15:05.000
GOD, I LOVE THAT PLACE.

15:05.000 --> 15:07.667
DON'T GET OUT
MUCH, DO YOU?

15:07.667 --> 15:08.250
ANYWAY,
I'M ANDIE MCPHEE.

15:08.250 --> 15:09.083
YOU'RE JOEY, RIGHT?

15:09.083 --> 15:10.625
I'M A FRIEND
OF PACEY WITTER'S.

15:10.625 --> 15:12.917
WELL, KIND OF.

15:12.917 --> 15:14.875
HOW BOLD OF YOU TO ADMIT THAT.

15:14.875 --> 15:16.041
ANYWAY,

15:16.041 --> 15:17.708
MY BROTHER JACK'S
LOOKING FOR A JOB.

15:17.708 --> 15:19.583
YOU KNOW, BUSBOY, WAITER,
REALLY ANYTHING,

15:19.583 --> 15:21.667
SO I THOUGHT I'D PUT IN
A WORD FOR HIM.

15:21.667 --> 15:22.750
WELL, ACTUALLY,
WE COULD USE THE HELP.

15:22.750 --> 15:25.500
REALLY?
OH, THAT'S GREAT!

15:25.500 --> 15:26.542
HE'S KIND OF SHY,

15:26.542 --> 15:28.125
BUT HE IS REALLY SMART
AND SUPER NICE,

15:28.125 --> 15:29.625
ONCE YOU GET TO KNOW HIM.

15:29.625 --> 15:31.750
OKAY, WELL, JUST TELL HIM
TO COME IN AND ASK FOR ME.

15:31.750 --> 15:35.458
ALL RIGHT! THANKS! THANKS A LOT.

15:40.125 --> 15:42.083
JOEY, HEY.

15:42.083 --> 15:44.417
HEY.

15:44.417 --> 15:45.625
I WAS, UM...

15:45.625 --> 15:46.792
THIS MIGHT SOUND WEIRD.

15:46.792 --> 15:49.000
I WAS CLEANING OUT
MY CLOSET THIS MORNING,

15:49.000 --> 15:50.875
AND I FOUND THE COSTUME

15:50.875 --> 15:51.625
THAT YOU WORE
IN MY MOVIE.

15:51.625 --> 15:54.583
I WAS JUST THINKING

15:54.583 --> 15:55.750
ABOUT HOW GOOD
YOU LOOKED IN IT.

15:55.750 --> 15:57.542
UM, YOU KNOW, HOW
PRETTY AND VULNERABLE,

15:57.542 --> 15:58.708
AND I WAS JUST
THINKING, YOU KNOW,

15:58.708 --> 16:01.000
"I HOPE JOEY WAS HAPPY
WITH HER PERFORMANCE

16:01.000 --> 16:02.166
IN THE MOVIE."

16:04.125 --> 16:05.458
I GUESS I'M ASKING--

16:05.458 --> 16:06.625
I'M SURPRISED WE HAVEN'T
DISCUSSED THIS BEFORE--

16:06.625 --> 16:10.750
BUT, UM, WHAT DID YOU
THINK OF MY MOVIE?

16:10.750 --> 16:11.959
I LOVED IT.
IT WAS GREAT.

16:11.959 --> 16:14.667
YOU KNOW THAT, DAWSON.

16:14.667 --> 16:17.166
YOU'D BE HONEST
WITH ME, RIGHT?

16:17.166 --> 16:17.792
IT WAS AMAZING.

16:17.792 --> 16:20.083
EXTREMELY TALENTED.

16:20.083 --> 16:24.125
IT'S ONE OF YOUR
MANY ATTRACTIONS.

16:24.125 --> 16:26.083
LOOK, ARE YOU
ALL RIGHT?

16:26.083 --> 16:27.083
NO, I JUST...

16:27.083 --> 16:29.250
I JUST WANTED TO MAKE SURE

16:29.250 --> 16:31.625
THAT YOU DIDN'T THINK MY MOVIE
WAS ON THE, UM...

16:31.625 --> 16:33.333
I DON'T KNOW,
STUPID AND PUTRID SIDE.

16:33.333 --> 16:35.750
YOU'RE ACTING WEIRD.

16:35.750 --> 16:36.500
ARE YOU HAVING
AN INSECURITY ATTACK?

16:36.500 --> 16:38.458
COME ON.

16:38.458 --> 16:40.917
IT'S JUST REALLY
IMPORTANT FOR ME

16:40.917 --> 16:42.166
TO KNOW THAT YOU THINK

16:42.166 --> 16:42.750
THAT I HAVE TALENT
AND POTENTIAL

16:42.750 --> 16:45.542
AS A FILMMAKER.

16:47.834 --> 16:49.208
YOU READ MY JOURNAL.

16:49.208 --> 16:52.333
YOU PRACTICALLY LEFT IT OUT
FOR ME TO SEE.

16:52.333 --> 16:54.667
OH, NOT UNLESS IT BLEW OPEN,

16:54.667 --> 16:56.000
OR YOU SUDDENLY DEVELOPED
X-RAY VISION.

16:56.000 --> 16:57.041
I MEAN, GOD!

16:57.041 --> 16:58.875
HOW DARE YOU?

16:58.875 --> 16:59.834
YOU INVADED MY PRIVACY.

16:59.834 --> 17:01.458
I MEAN,
I COULD SUE YOU FOR THIS.

17:01.458 --> 17:03.834
WHAT I'M CURIOUS ABOUT
IS WHAT ELSE IS IN THAT JOURNAL

17:03.834 --> 17:04.791
THAT YOU DON'T WANT ME TO SEE?

17:04.791 --> 17:05.458
WHAT ELSE DOES
JOEY POTTER

17:05.458 --> 17:07.290
REALLY THINK OF ME?

17:07.290 --> 17:09.000
OH, RIGHT NOW, DAWSON,
YOU REALLY DON'T WANT TO KNOW.

17:14.333 --> 17:16.165
HEY, COLE.

17:16.165 --> 17:16.834
HEY, MITCH.
WHAT'S UP?

17:16.834 --> 17:19.208
OH, NOT MUCH.

17:19.208 --> 17:20.541
HEY, BUDDY.

17:20.541 --> 17:23.375
JUST CHECKING OUT
A WAREHOUSE NEXT DOOR

17:23.375 --> 17:25.916
AS A POSSIBLE
RESTAURANT LOCATION.

17:25.916 --> 17:27.875
VERY COOL. AND?

17:27.875 --> 17:29.917
RENT'S A LITTLE STEEP.

17:29.917 --> 17:32.208
TELL ME ABOUT IT.

17:32.208 --> 17:34.208
OKAY, BUDDY, WHAT'S REALLY UP?

17:34.208 --> 17:37.208
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
WHAT'S UP?

17:37.208 --> 17:38.208
NOTHING.

17:38.208 --> 17:39.166
WHATEVER.

17:39.166 --> 17:40.875
YOU KNOW, LIFE.

17:40.875 --> 17:41.875
MITCH, I'VE KNOWN YOU

17:41.875 --> 17:43.750
SINCE WE WERE
IN THE FOURTH GRADE.

17:43.750 --> 17:44.875
YOU LOOK LIKE YOU'VE GOT

17:44.875 --> 17:45.792
THE WEIGHT OF THE WORLD
ON YOUR SHOULDERS.

17:45.792 --> 17:47.333
TALK TO ME.

18:00.166 --> 18:02.792
IT WAS SO KIND OF YOU

18:02.792 --> 18:03.875
TO SEND OVER THAT
DELICIOUS CASSEROLE

18:03.875 --> 18:06.250
WHEN MR. RYAN PASSED.

18:06.250 --> 18:09.333
IT WAS THE LEAST
I COULD DO.

18:09.333 --> 18:10.417
UM...

18:10.417 --> 18:13.041
I WAS WONDERING, UH...

18:13.041 --> 18:14.792
THE THING IS,

18:14.792 --> 18:15.583
MRS. RYAN,

18:15.583 --> 18:19.542
I COULD REALLY USE SOME ADVICE.

18:19.542 --> 18:21.417
MY ADVICE,

18:21.417 --> 18:23.834
YOU'VE GOT TO AVOID
THE BIG "D"

18:23.834 --> 18:24.917
AT ALL COSTS, MAN.

18:24.917 --> 18:26.917
BUT WE'VE TRIED
EVERYTHING, YOU KNOW?

18:26.917 --> 18:28.041
I MEAN,

18:28.041 --> 18:30.000
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S LEFT.

18:30.000 --> 18:32.583
MY BROTHER,
IF YOU GET DIVORCED,

18:32.583 --> 18:34.750
YOU ARE GOING
TO LOSE EVERYTHING.

18:34.750 --> 18:36.959
NOT TO MENTION BECOME
A WEEKEND DADDY TO DAWSON.

18:36.959 --> 18:37.625
BELIEVE ME, I KNOW.

18:37.625 --> 18:40.083
YOU KNOW,

18:40.083 --> 18:40.917
I DON'T EVEN THINK
SHE WOULD MIND

18:40.917 --> 18:43.708
IF I HAD AN AFFAIR.

18:43.708 --> 18:45.250
LET HER OFF THE HOOK.

18:45.250 --> 18:46.542
SO WHY NOT?

18:46.542 --> 18:49.000
WHAT DO YOU MEAN, "WHY NOT?"

18:49.000 --> 18:50.917
I'M IN A MARRIAGE.

18:50.917 --> 18:51.708
MARRIAGE IS ALL ABOUT

18:51.708 --> 18:53.917
ENDURING
THE EBBS AND FLOWS.

18:53.917 --> 18:55.291
YOU MUST DO EVERYTHING
AND ANYTHING

18:55.291 --> 18:57.500
IN YOUR POWER
TO SAVE IT.

18:57.500 --> 19:00.291
BELIEVE ME, I HAVE TALKED
UNTIL I AM BLUE IN THE FACE.

19:00.291 --> 19:02.083
I'VE CLEANED OUT
THE ENTIRE MARITAL AIDS SECTION

19:02.083 --> 19:04.458
AT THE PLEASURE PALACE,

19:04.458 --> 19:07.291
AND MY VICTORIA'S SECRET
CREDIT CARD IS MAXED.

19:07.291 --> 19:09.834
I WAS THINKING
MORE ALONG THE LINES

19:09.834 --> 19:10.625
OF SOMETHING LIKE

19:10.625 --> 19:12.417
RENEWING YOUR
WEDDING VOWS.

19:12.417 --> 19:15.291
I WASN'T SUGGESTING
THAT YOU HAVE AN AFFAIR.

19:15.291 --> 19:16.125
AN AFFAIR WON'T FIX IT.

19:16.125 --> 19:18.125
I'M NOT SUGGESTING
AN AFFAIR.

19:18.125 --> 19:20.750
I'M TALKING
OPEN MARRIAGE.

19:20.750 --> 19:23.792
[SCOFFS]

19:23.792 --> 19:26.917
I KNEW THAT THE '70S
WERE BACK IN FULL SWING, MAN,

19:26.917 --> 19:28.333
BUT THAT IS
RIGHT UP THERE

19:28.333 --> 19:29.875
WITH BEAN BAG CHAIRS
AND LAVA LAMPS.

19:29.875 --> 19:31.417
NOW, JUST THINK ABOUT
THIS FOR A MINUTE,

19:31.417 --> 19:32.375
ALL RIGHT?

19:32.375 --> 19:33.667
IN ANY GIVEN MARRIAGE,

19:33.667 --> 19:34.875
STATISTICALLY YOU'VE
GOT AN 85% CHANCE

19:34.875 --> 19:36.083
OF INFIDELITY.

19:36.083 --> 19:38.166
HUMAN BEINGS
ARE JUST NOT

19:38.166 --> 19:39.333
INSTINCTIVELY
MONOGAMOUS.

19:39.333 --> 19:40.291
ALL RIGHT?

19:40.291 --> 19:41.625
SO YOU TAKE

19:41.625 --> 19:43.834
THE ANTIQUATED NOTION
OF FIDELITY AND MONOGAMY

19:43.834 --> 19:44.834
OUT OF MARRIAGE,

19:44.834 --> 19:46.500
AND I PROMISE YOU,
I GUARANTEE YOU

19:46.500 --> 19:47.291
THAT THE DIVORCE RATE
IN THIS COUNTRY

19:47.291 --> 19:48.959
WOULD BE ABSOLUTELY ZILCH.

19:50.834 --> 19:52.250
WORKS FOR ME AND LISA.

20:03.500 --> 20:06.834
YOU KNOW, I HATE IT
WHEN PEOPLE PLASTER

20:06.834 --> 20:07.959
UNSOLICITED MATERIAL
ON PRIVATE PROPERTY.

20:07.959 --> 20:09.500
YOU KNOW WHAT,
MCPHEE?

20:09.500 --> 20:11.542
I REALLY WISH YOU WEREN'T HERE
RIGHT NOW.

20:11.542 --> 20:14.291
PUT THE CHARM ON HOLD
FOR A SECOND, PACEY.

20:14.291 --> 20:15.041
I WAS JUST CURIOUS
WHAT THE OCCASION'S FOR.

20:15.041 --> 20:17.375
IT'S MY GOING AWAY PARTY.

20:17.375 --> 20:18.959
I'M DYING OF A HEART STRIPE,
OR HADN'T YOU HEARD?

20:18.959 --> 20:20.000
WHERE'S YOUR
SENSE OF HUMOR?

20:20.000 --> 20:21.083
OH, I HAVE
A SENSE OF HUMOR.

20:21.083 --> 20:23.208
IN FACT, I HAVE A REALLY GOOD
SENSE OF HUMOR.

20:23.208 --> 20:24.417
IT'S JUST THAT
TELLING A GIRL

20:24.417 --> 20:26.250
THAT I'M DYING SO
SHE'LL GO OUT WITH ME,

20:26.250 --> 20:27.792
THAT'S JUST NOT FUNNY.

20:27.792 --> 20:29.083
WHY YOU WOULD BE
INTERESTED IN SOMEONE

20:29.083 --> 20:30.708
WHO IS SO MENTALLY DEFICIENT

20:30.708 --> 20:31.959
THAT SHE WOULD
ACTUALLY BELIEVE

20:31.959 --> 20:33.583
THERE'S SUCH A THING
AS A HEART STRIPE...

20:33.583 --> 20:34.875
OKAY, OKAY.

20:34.875 --> 20:36.041
I'M SORRY. TRUCE.

20:36.041 --> 20:38.083
SO REALLY,

20:38.083 --> 20:38.750
WHAT'S THE REASON
FOR YOUR LITTLE CLAMBAKE?

20:38.750 --> 20:40.834
OH, I'M SORRY.

20:40.834 --> 20:41.625
WERE YOU UNDER
THE MISTAKEN IMPRESSION

20:41.625 --> 20:43.250
THAT YOU WERE ACTUALLY INVITED?

20:43.250 --> 20:44.500
WELL, IT SAYS,
"COME ONE, COME ALL."

20:44.500 --> 20:47.291
NO, YOU'VE GOT TO READ
THE FINE PRINT.

20:47.291 --> 20:48.959
IT SAYS, "COME ON, COME ALL,

20:48.959 --> 20:50.208
"EXCEPT SPOILED
TRUST FUND CASUALTIES

20:50.208 --> 20:51.667
FROM RHODE ISLAND."

20:51.667 --> 20:53.417
HMM.

20:53.417 --> 20:54.625
SORRY.

20:54.625 --> 20:55.834
HMM.

20:57.375 --> 20:59.083
THIS IS CHARLIE,

20:59.083 --> 21:01.375
THE GUY I WAS
TELLING YOU ABOUT.

21:01.375 --> 21:03.458
OH, MY GOD.

21:03.458 --> 21:04.875
LOOK AT HIM.

21:04.875 --> 21:06.500
OH, GOD,

21:06.500 --> 21:09.166
I WOULD THROW MY
MOTHER OFF A BRIDGE

21:09.166 --> 21:11.083
TO GO OUT WITH
SOMEBODY LIKE THIS.

21:11.083 --> 21:13.583
WE PARTIED IN ATLANTIC CITY
ONE WEEKEND

21:13.583 --> 21:15.708
BEFORE HE HAD TO SHIP OUT.

21:15.708 --> 21:16.250
CRAZY.

21:16.250 --> 21:17.417
I CAN'T BELIEVE

21:17.417 --> 21:19.166
THAT YOU HAVE EYES
FOR DAWSON LEERY.

21:19.166 --> 21:23.125
I MEAN, YOU HAVE
LIVED, SISTER.

21:23.125 --> 21:26.417
SPEAKING OF PARTYING,

21:26.417 --> 21:28.375
SINCE YOU'RE NOT
HANGING OUT

21:28.375 --> 21:29.875
WITH FORREST GUMP
AND COMPANY ANYMORE,

21:29.875 --> 21:30.917
I WAS THINKING

21:30.917 --> 21:34.375
WE COULD DO SOME
SERIOUS PARTYING OF OUR OWN.

21:34.375 --> 21:35.542
WHAT,

21:35.542 --> 21:37.417
LIKE STEAL A PACK OF CIGARETTES
FROM 7-ELEVEN

21:37.417 --> 21:39.834
AND SMOKE THEM
BEHIND THE BLEACHERS?

21:39.834 --> 21:40.959
NO.
I DON'T THINK SO.

21:40.959 --> 21:43.500
I WAS THINKING
PACEY'S BOGUS DOCK PARTY.

21:43.500 --> 21:47.458
I MEAN, WE COULD CRACK
ON THE PEOPLE THERE...

21:47.458 --> 21:48.417
AND...

21:50.750 --> 21:52.625
A LITTLE IMPORTED BUBBLY
FOR OUR ENJOYMENT.

21:58.166 --> 21:59.750
ALL RIGHT, SO I SHOULDN'T
HAVE READ YOUR JOURNAL,

21:59.750 --> 22:00.959
BUT COME ON,
YOU CAN'T TELL ME

22:00.959 --> 22:01.875
ALL THE TIME YOU'VE
BEEN ALONE IN MY ROOM

22:01.875 --> 22:03.375
THAT YOU'VE
NEVER SNOOPED.

22:03.375 --> 22:04.333
NO.

22:04.333 --> 22:05.458
NOT ONCE?

22:05.458 --> 22:08.125
NO, BECAUSE I, UNLIKE YOU,
RESPECT YOUR PRIVACY.

22:08.125 --> 22:09.792
YOU OBVIOUSLY
DON'T RESPECT

22:09.792 --> 22:10.834
MY FILMMAKING ABILITIES.

22:10.834 --> 22:11.959
DAWSON, HOW I FEEL

22:11.959 --> 22:13.333
ABOUT YOU AND YOUR QUEST
TO BE SPIELBERG, JR.

22:13.333 --> 22:14.333
IS NOT THE POINT.

22:14.333 --> 22:15.708
YOU READ MY JOURNAL.

22:15.708 --> 22:17.291
THIS IS A HUGE PRIVACY ISSUE.

22:17.291 --> 22:18.667
JOEY, THAT'S
EXACTLY THE POINT.

22:18.667 --> 22:19.959
HOW YOU FEEL
ABOUT MY FILMMAKING--

22:19.959 --> 22:21.166
HI. I'M, UH, JACK.

22:21.166 --> 22:22.500
CAN I HELP YOU?

22:22.500 --> 22:23.500
ANDIE'S BROTHER.

22:23.500 --> 22:24.834
WHO'S ANDIE?

22:24.834 --> 22:26.083
MY SISTER.

22:26.083 --> 22:27.667
LOOK, THAT'S FASCINATING,
AND I DON'T MEAN TO BE RUDE,

22:27.667 --> 22:31.041
BUT AS YOU CAN SEE,
I'M REALLY BUSY HERE, SO--

22:31.041 --> 22:33.000
I'M HERE TO INTERVIEW
FOR THE JOB.

22:33.000 --> 22:34.083
OH, YEAH, RIGHT.

22:34.083 --> 22:35.792
JACK, ANDIE'S BROTHER.

22:35.792 --> 22:38.667
UM, LISTEN, HAVE YOU EVER
WASHED DISHES BEFORE?

22:38.667 --> 22:40.625
NO, BUT I'M WILLING TO LEARN.

22:40.625 --> 22:41.667
GOOD. INTERVIEW'S OVER.
KITCHEN'S THAT WAY.

22:46.291 --> 22:47.291
I ADMIT,

22:47.291 --> 22:48.250
WHAT I DID
WAS WRONG,

22:48.250 --> 22:49.333
BUT, JOEY,
YOU LIED TO ME.

22:49.333 --> 22:50.625
YOU'VE BEEN
LYING TO ME.

22:50.625 --> 22:52.500
DON'T TURN THIS AROUND
AND MAKE ME THE BAD GUY, DAWSON.

22:52.500 --> 22:53.750
YOU VIOLATED ME.
YOU BETRAYED ME.

22:53.750 --> 22:55.750
TELL ME, WERE YOU EVER PLANNING
ON TELLING ME THE TRUTH?

22:55.750 --> 22:57.291
WHY SHOULD I?

22:57.291 --> 22:58.708
I THOUGHT I'D JUST
WRITE IT ALL DOWN

22:58.708 --> 22:59.458
AND THEN HAVE YOU OVER TO STUDY.

22:59.458 --> 23:00.208
STOP MAKING JOKES,
JOEY.

23:00.208 --> 23:02.250
