THEY'RE IN KENTUCKY.

38:02.750 --> 38:04.208
ABBY, THAT DOESN'T HELP.

38:04.208 --> 38:05.375
WHAT?

38:08.542 --> 38:11.250
OH, WOULD YOU LOOK AT ME?

38:11.250 --> 38:12.375
I'M A MESS.

38:12.375 --> 38:13.667
DON'T SAY THAT.

38:13.667 --> 38:16.125
YOU HAVE MORE STYLE
AND SEX APPEAL

38:16.125 --> 38:17.250
IN YOUR LITTLE FINGER

38:17.250 --> 38:17.417
THAN THAT WHITE TRASH LOSER.

38:20.792 --> 38:22.542
I WANT HIM BACK.

38:24.542 --> 38:25.458
GOD, WHY?

38:29.708 --> 38:31.750
BECAUSE I LOVE HIM.

38:31.750 --> 38:34.959
LOOK,
THAT'S JUST THE BOOZE TALKING.

38:34.959 --> 38:35.959
NO.

38:35.959 --> 38:37.917
NO, I'M SERIOUS.

38:37.917 --> 38:40.959
I LOVE HIM AND I WANT HIM BACK.

38:40.959 --> 38:45.000
ALL RIGHT,

38:45.000 --> 38:47.500
THEN WE'RE GOING
TO GET HIM BACK FOR YOU.

38:51.583 --> 38:54.792
OKAY.

39:02.083 --> 39:05.041
THIS IS FOR YOU.

39:05.041 --> 39:07.750
IT'S NOT MUCH.

39:07.750 --> 39:09.333
WELL, IT IS
YOUR BIRTHDAY,

39:09.333 --> 39:10.500
ISN'T IT?

39:10.500 --> 39:13.667
HOW'D YOU KNOW?

39:13.667 --> 39:15.500
I'M PSYCHIC.

39:15.500 --> 39:17.125
OKAY, I HEARD YOU
AND THAT GUY DAWSON

39:17.125 --> 39:18.291
ARGUING ABOUT IT.

39:18.291 --> 39:19.917
I HAD IT IN MY CAR.

39:19.917 --> 39:23.542
I MEAN, I WAS GOING TO GIVE IT
TO MY BROTHER FOR CHRISTMAS,

39:23.542 --> 39:24.875
BUT I KIND OF, WELL,
FORGOT ABOUT IT.

39:27.166 --> 39:29.750
ANYWAY, GO AHEAD,
OPEN IT.

39:41.708 --> 39:43.041
ASK IT A QUESTION.

39:43.041 --> 39:47.125
WILL I PASS MY DRIVER'S TEST
ON THE NEXT TRY?

39:49.000 --> 39:50.417
"SIGNS POINT TO YES."

39:53.208 --> 39:54.959
WHAT IS MY FUTURE?

39:58.542 --> 39:59.041
HEH. "CANNOT PREDICT NOW."

39:59.041 --> 40:00.041
YOUR TURN.

40:00.041 --> 40:02.417
OKAY.

40:02.417 --> 40:03.834
OH, NO!

40:05.041 --> 40:06.917
OH...

40:06.917 --> 40:09.208
THAT CAN'T BE
A GOOD SIGN.

40:09.208 --> 40:10.041
HMM...

40:10.041 --> 40:12.291
I'M SORRY.

40:12.291 --> 40:13.708
IT'S THE THOUGHT
THAT COUNTS.

40:13.708 --> 40:18.834
I HAVE ALWAYS BEEN
THIS COMPLETE KLUTZ.

40:18.834 --> 40:21.250
SOME THINGS
NEVER CHANGE.

40:21.250 --> 40:24.750
NO. EVERYTHING CHANGES.

40:24.750 --> 40:27.750
EVERYBODY CHANGES.
EXCEPT FOR ME.

40:27.750 --> 40:31.583
TAKE THIS WHOLE STUPID PARTY,
FOR EXAMPLE.

40:31.583 --> 40:32.875
I THOUGHT I COULD AT LEAST BE

40:32.875 --> 40:36.166
"PACEY WITTER, THE GUY
WHO THROWS A GOOD PARTY,"

40:36.166 --> 40:38.125
BUT NO, I'M STILL JUST

40:38.125 --> 40:40.208
"PACEY WITTER, THE GUY
WHO'S FAILING BIOLOGY,"

40:40.208 --> 40:41.500
BUT NOW I'M A YEAR OLDER.

40:43.208 --> 40:44.083
YOU KNOW, MAYBE YOU'RE JUST

40:44.083 --> 40:46.333
"PACEY WITTER,

40:46.333 --> 40:48.291
THE GUY WHO'S STILL TRYING
TO FIGURE IT OUT."

40:51.041 --> 40:52.708
WOW.

40:52.708 --> 40:54.583
WHAT?

40:54.583 --> 40:58.834
WE ARE SO...

40:58.834 --> 40:59.875
DEEP.

41:26.875 --> 41:28.792
DO YOU THINK
YOU CAN GET HOME OKAY?

41:29.375 --> 41:30.458
I'VE GOT TO GO BACK.

41:30.458 --> 41:32.959
I'VE GOT TO TRY
AND TALK TO PACEY.

41:32.959 --> 41:33.959
OH.

41:33.959 --> 41:38.917
YEAH.

41:38.917 --> 41:40.542
OKAY.

41:47.333 --> 41:49.750
I'LL BE FINE.

41:52.208 --> 41:53.667
♪ BLONDE HAIR, BLUE EYES ♪

41:53.667 --> 41:55.834
♪ IN THE NIGHT
SHE CRIES AND CRIES ♪

41:55.834 --> 42:00.333
♪ SAD GIRL WITH YOUNG EYES
HOLDS A GUN AT HER SIDE ♪

42:00.333 --> 42:05.583
♪ MARY... ♪♪

42:10.834 --> 42:14.291
AH, THE PERFECT END
TO A PERFECT PARTY.

42:14.291 --> 42:16.166
PACEY, I'VE BEEN

42:16.166 --> 42:17.500
A REALLY LOUSY FRIEND
LATELY, AND...

42:17.500 --> 42:20.041
THERE'S NO EXCUSE FOR
FORGETTING YOUR BIRTHDAY,

42:20.041 --> 42:22.667
BUT IT'S NOT BECAUSE
I'VE WRITTEN YOU OFF.

42:22.667 --> 42:23.834
IT'S JUST THIS--
THIS JOEY THING

42:23.834 --> 42:28.875
HAS BEEN SO INCREDIBLY
CONFUSING AND COMPLICATED--

42:28.875 --> 42:30.583
DAWSON, DAWSON, DAWSON,
IT'S OKAY, MAN.

42:30.583 --> 42:31.542
I FORGIVE YOU.

42:31.542 --> 42:33.125
I'M HAPPY
FOR YOU TWO.

42:33.125 --> 42:34.417
YOU DESERVE
HAPPINESS.

42:34.417 --> 42:36.041
GOD KNOWS IT TOOK
LONG ENOUGH.

42:36.041 --> 42:38.708
THE ONLY THING
THAT I WAS TRYING TO SAY

42:38.708 --> 42:39.708
IS THERE ARE CERTAIN THINGS

42:39.708 --> 42:42.875
THAT I'M GOING TO MISS,
AS YOUR FRIEND.

42:42.875 --> 42:44.875
THAT'S NATURAL.
IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

42:44.875 --> 42:47.625
BUT TO ME
IT'S A VERY BIG DEAL.

42:47.625 --> 42:50.041
MAYBE MY ACTIONS HAVEN'T EXACTLY
SHOWN THAT LATELY,

42:50.041 --> 42:52.875
BUT IT'S JUST BECAUSE EVERYTHING
IS REALLY COMPLICATED

42:52.875 --> 42:54.708
AND EVERYTHING'S CHANGING,

42:54.708 --> 42:55.708
BUT NOTHING
IS EVER GONNA CHANGE SO MUCH

42:55.708 --> 42:57.834
THAT YOU'RE NOT GONNA BE
MY BEST FRIEND.

43:04.375 --> 43:06.458
ARE WE HAVING A MOMENT HERE?

43:06.458 --> 43:07.708
I THINK WE ARE.

43:09.250 --> 43:10.834
LET'S GO.
YEAH.

43:15.083 --> 43:17.250
IT'S REALLY TOO BAD
ABOUT YOUR LICENSE.

43:17.250 --> 43:18.166
THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

43:18.166 --> 43:19.208
I CAN TAKE
THE TEST AGAIN

43:19.208 --> 43:20.041
IN A COUPLE OF WEEKS.

43:21.291 --> 43:22.917
MAYBE YOU NEED
SOME MORE PRACTICE.

43:22.917 --> 43:24.208
PLEASE. YOU AND I
BOTH KNOW

43:24.208 --> 43:25.917
I'VE BEEN BREAKING
THAT STATE LAW

43:25.917 --> 43:27.417
FOR AT LEAST
THE LAST THREE YEARS.

43:27.417 --> 43:28.667
I MEAN, RIGHT NOW.

43:28.667 --> 43:29.583
WHAT?

43:29.583 --> 43:31.250
YOU AND ME. MAINE.
RIGHT NOW.

43:31.250 --> 43:34.125
WHAT?
I KNOW WHERE THE KEYS
TO THE MITCHMOBILE ARE.

43:34.125 --> 43:35.792
OH, PLEASE, DAWSON.
YOUR FATHER WOULD
KILL YOU.

43:35.792 --> 43:38.792
DON'T WUSS OUT
ON ME NOW, PACEY.

43:38.792 --> 43:40.417
LISTEN, DAWSON,
WE'RE COOL, MAN.

43:40.417 --> 43:42.041
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO DO THIS.

43:42.041 --> 43:44.083
SHUT UP.
MAYBE I WANT TO.

43:51.333 --> 43:52.333
PACEY?

43:52.333 --> 43:53.417
YEAH?

43:53.417 --> 43:56.083
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

43:56.083 --> 44:02.542
THANKS, BRO.

